  "time_ut": 1658212029,
  "original_lang": "si",
  "original_title": "\u0d89\u0db1\u0dca\u0db0\u0db1 \u0d85\u0dbb\u0dca\u0db6\u0dd4\u0daf\u0dba\u0dd9\u0db1\u0dca \u0db6\u0dd0\u0da7\u0d9a\u0db1 \u0db0\u0dd3\u0dc0\u0dbb\u0dba\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Fishermen suffering from fuel crisis",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Mannar Fishermen's Associations point out that nearly 2000 fishermen families are suffering due to severe shortage of fuel in Mannar due to which the fishermen in Mannar have not traveled for almost one and a half months.",
        "Due to the lack of fuel for the fishing vessels, a large number of fishermen have been unable to go to sea and the economy of the fishermen has been severely affected, according to the Mannar Fishermen's Association.",
        "Also, due to fishermen not going to sea, the price of fish in Mannar has increased excessively, where Kutti fish, Thalapat, Thora, Mora, Kelawalla, Balaya etc. fish are sold at a price of nearly 2500 rupees, the consumers are also in dire straits.",
        "Also, although fish was transported from Mannar to Colombo to various areas in the past, the fish transport has stopped completely due to lack of fuel, Mannar fishermen say.",
        "Meanwhile, the Mannar fishermen's associations have further requested the authorities to implement some assistance program for the fishermen in Mannar as their daily economy has been severely affected due to their inability to go to the sea to catch fish."
      ],
